pull_request.body:
This pull request refactors and optimizes several core utilities and encoding/decoding logic in the `QsNet` library, focusing on performance, correctness, and code clarity. Key changes include more efficient handling of collections, improved duplicate and merging logic, and enhancements to encoding and decoding routines. The changes are grouped below by theme.

### Decoder and Encoder Optimizations

* Refactored the handling of split query string parts in `Decoder.cs` to avoid unnecessary allocations, improve limit enforcement, and pre-size collections for performance.
* Improved duplicate key handling in decoded query strings, now supporting `Combine`, `Last`, and `First` strategies with clearer logic.
* Added an `IdentityFormatter` to `Encoder.cs` to avoid per-call lambda allocations and streamlined formatter assignment. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5R16-R17) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5L63-R65)
* Optimized sequence detection and materialization in `Encoder.cs` for more efficient access and to avoid repeated enumeration. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5R147-R168) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5L178-R239)
* Enhanced encoding logic for dictionaries, arrays, and lists, including fast paths for common generic dictionaries and improved key encoding for dot notation. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5R254-R282) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5R294-R298) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5L273-R348) [[4]](diffhunk://#diff-fcf69a53d04f956f4b51ecd0d809c4c79272756d23ee372d41763335453d92b5L301-R373)

### Utils Improvements

* Improved merging logic in `Utils.cs` for lists and sets, ensuring correct handling of `Undefined` values and more efficient concatenation and set addition. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL149-R176) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL192-R215)
* Refactored the `Apply` method to avoid LINQ allocation and use explicit loops for better performance.
* Replaced LINQ `.Any()` with a custom `HasAny` helper for more efficient empty checks on enumerables.

### Dictionary and Collection Handling

* Optimized dictionary copying and normalization by using direct enumeration and pre-sizing, and improved detection of self-referential maps. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL805-R850) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL976-R1031)
* Improved nested value conversion in dictionaries and collections, using explicit copying and enumeration for better performance and reliability. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL870-R918) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL881-R930) [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-d6d00580c30cce84e82a906209cc9cdd38f667af22adc290a3fec7d3a3287d8aL1008-R1058)

These changes collectively improve the reliability and efficiency of query string parsing and encoding, as well as utility functions for collection manipulation and normalization.

Switch pre-commit to prek (#54258)

The pre-commit is a fantastic tool, and we heavily used it for years,
but generally the tool stagnated and is not showing a sign of adapting
to our needs. For years we tried to convince pre-commit maintainers that
things like autocomplete are necessary - but it met with pretty much
resistance (if not hostility) from the maintainer. Also there was no
chance for them to accept expectations of bigger projects like ours,
where we have a huge monorepo and not only multiple needs but also
different parts of the repo needing different language support (golang,
typescript soon) - and apparenty the maintainer of pre-commit does not
think monorepo is a good thing at all. Similarly - they did not recognize
the raise of `uv` and the only way to use `uv` with pre-commit is to patch
it by installing `pre-comit-uv` that essentialy patches pre-commit with
uv support. This is not really sustainable and the tool lags behind many
of our needs.

Luckily - we have new project in town - prek - which rewrites pre-commit
that is 100% compatible (now), 10x faster (because rust), uses `uv`
natively, supports auto-complete already and they have very friendly
maintainer who is not only supporting us but also very happily works
on improving `prek` to close all the gaps, and plans to implement (with
our support of course and cooperation) monorepo support - that will
allow us to modularise our pre-commits.

This PR switches our pre-commit support to use prek exclusively:

* breeze static checks command is completely removed
* custom auto-complete code in breeze as well
* instructions are updated to setup prek instead of precommit
* CI is updated to run prek instead of pre-commmit
* documentation for static checks is reviewed and new features that
  prek enables are added
Remove db dependency for apprise notifier tests (#54578)
Fix few small typos in prek documentation/diagnostics (#54586)

Fix prek teething errors for canary builds (#54583)

After switching to prek in #54258 there are still few small things
thet were only discovered in our canary builds:

* installation of prek hooks does not necessarily create
  uv cache
* autoupgrade is not yet implemented in prek

pull_request.title: Update workflow to write documentation files to `/documentation/` directory
pull_request.body:
This PR updates the GitHub workflow to organize documentation files in a dedicated `/documentation/` directory instead of cluttering the repository root.

## Changes Made

**Workflow Updates (`download-docs.yml`):**
- Added `mkdir -p documentation` to create the directory if it doesn't exist
- Changed file save location from `${name}.md` to `documentation/${name}.md`
- Updated git commands from `git add *.md` to `git add documentation/`

**Repository Structure:**
- Moved all existing documentation files to the new `/documentation/` directory
- Maintains clean separation between workflow files, configuration, and documentation

## Before/After

**Before:** Documentation files scattered in root
```
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .github/workflows/download-docs.yml
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docs.csv
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ bun.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ DaisyUI.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Svelte5.md
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
```

**After:** Documentation organized in dedicated directory
```
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ .github/workflows/download-docs.yml
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ docs.csv
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ documentation/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ bun.md
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ DaisyUI.md
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Svelte5.md
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
```

The workflow will now automatically create the `/documentation/` folder and save all downloaded documentation files there, providing better organization and keeping the repository root clean.

Fixes #4.

issue.body:
**What this PR does / why we need it**:
The nightly build fails from time to time on unit tests, when trying to create dashboard handlers based on a non-exists directory of dashboard yamls.

The directory name is computed with:
```go
dir := path.Join(os.TempDir(), fmt.Sprint(time.Now().UTC().Unix()))
```

This pattern is used in two additional unit tests. The guess is that the directory is aleady exist, when the tests assumes it isn't.

This commit gives a unique directory name for each one of the tests that uses the temp directory name pattern, to ensure each test is using its own directory. Also, try to make these test more robust, by taking logic out of the `By` functions, and by adding some error checks.

**Release note**:
